message.content:
I need to identify tangible items that are held for use in the production or supply of goods, rental, or administrative purposes.

In a balance sheet, these items are typically categorized as "Fixed Assets" or "Property, Plant and Equipment (PP&E)". Fixed assets are tangible assets used in operations over multiple periods.

Looking at the balance sheet provided:
- "Fixed Assets" is listed with an initial amount of 5000000.00 on 2023-12-31
- "Fixed Assets" has an end amount of 7265288.42 on 2024-01-29

The "Fixed Assets" line item represents tangible items used in business operations, so this is the item I need to extract.

{"solution": {'initial value': '5000000.00', 'end value': '7265288.42'} }
